The need for child care in order for the applicant or recipient to participate in or to continue participation in the activities or to accept employment, where appropriate and affordable child care (formal or informal) is not available within a
        reasonable distance from the applicant&#8217;s or recipient&#8217;s home or service site. For purposes of this paragraph, there is a need for child care if the applicant or recipient is caring for a child under six (6) years of age or
        for a child who has special health care needs (verified by competent medical evidence, as determined by the Director or his or her designee) that prevents regular attendance at school;

Resides in a location which is so remote from a program or activity that transportation is not available. The individual shall be considered remote if a round trip of more than two (2) hours by reasonably available public or private transportation,
        exclusive of time necessary to transport children to and from a child care facility or school, would be required for a normal work or training day. However, if normal commuting time in the area is more than two (2) hours, then the round trip commuting
        time shall not be considered good cause;
